                                        <h2 class="text-muted card-subtitle main-title-bg">Introduction<br></h2>
                                        <p>A software system and its rules for directing operations make up a business rules engine. It executes one or more business rules in a runtime productive environment to automate decisions based on loaded predetermined circumstances.<br><br>The guidelines for a BRE may be drawn from corporate policy, legal requirements, or other significant sources that must be followed. Even without coding experience, a worker with the appropriate authorization can modify this software.<br><br>This amount of decision automation is possible because of the business rules engine. Enterprises may create, install, and manage business rules and decision logic with the help of these software solutions, enabling applications to make wise judgments reliably, rapidly, and with the least amount of human involvement. BRE transform the rules that guide business choices into corporate assets that may be used in workflows throughout the company.<br></p>
